    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="797"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Count Bismarck</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Judd</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-27">
                        <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 27, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>The royal government is profoundly moved by the intelligence which reached here
                    yesterday of the assassination of President Lincoln, and the simultaneous
                    attempt on the life of the Secretary of State, Mr. Seward.</p>
                <p>In view of the so happily existing friendly relations between Prussia and the
                    United States, the undersigned cannot forbear to express to their government the
                    sincere sympathy of the royal government with the great loss that this crime has
                    inflicted upon them. He therefore requests the envoy extraordinary and minister
                    plenipotentiary of the United States of America, Mr. Judd, that he will convey
                    the expression of these sentiments to his government, and he avails himself of
                    this occasion to renew to Mr. Judd the assurances of his distinguished
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BISMARCK.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">N. B. Judd</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,
                            &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
